info.other: No accuracy on geolocation reference.[;]Appears to be a collection of 12 arrowheads and arrowhead fragments individually listed in side profile drawings on reverse. As follows from left column top-to-bottom to right column top-to-bottom.[;]L 35, W 13, Wt 6gms - midrib, fairly decayed, blade only.[;]L 34, W 14, Wt 3.5gms - Angular, diamond shaped, multiple bevels, blade only.[;]L 47, W 15, Wt 5gms - Somewhat diamond shaped, likely socketed and barbed, tang socket creates tapering midrib.[;]L 48, W 16, Wt 17gms - Triangular, tanged and barbed, tang quite small, tip square and blunt probably missing.[;]L 66, Wbl 12, Wsocket 10, Wt 7gms - Probably quite damaged and decayed, tang/socket? nearly as long as blade.[;]L 16, W 8, Wt 1gm. - Fragment, portion of blade.[;]L 12, W 9, Wt 1.5gms - Fragment, portion of blade.[;]L 18, W 7, Wt 1gm. - Triangular, relatively thick tang, mid rib or depression, edge bevels.[;]L 16, W 10, Wt 2gms - Triangular, barbed and tanged, tang quite short and stout, barb worn away on one side.[;]L 20, W 9, Wt 1.5gms - Somewhat triangular, possibly socketed?
info.collection: Chadwick Museum[;]Bolton

info.other: No accuracy on geolocation reference.[;]5 side profile drawings of arrow heads on reverse as follows.[;]A with text "8mm thick" pointing to midrib and "tang bent" pointing to tang near blade. Tang quite long, barbed, pointed tip.[;]B with text 12mm thick pointing to blade where it meets tang. Also a top cross section profile of blade which is diamond shaped. Tang is quite long, and merges into blade where it wraps around to barbs.[;]C with text "11mm thick" pointing to blade just above tang, and "tang bent" pointing to tang just below blade, tang and barbs quite long.[;]D with text "8.5mm thick" pointing to blade at tang., tang is drawn bent to one side, barbs extant but blunted and worn down. Blade triangular with some chips and blunted, square tip.[;]E with text "12mm thick" pointing to bottom of blade where it meets tang. Very triangular shaped, tanged with no barbs.[;]Also text on reverse of card "All sections similar to section of B" referring to diamond-shaped top cross-section.
